title: Label printer - not working / no response
text: Log the customer out of the system all the way to the client login and make sure they are logged in on the right machine. Machine Login: If they open it from POS = DdDPOS If they open it on a BO machine = Backoffice Ask them to shut off printer, then restart POS (or PC), then turn printer on again. __________________________________________________________________________________________________ Otherwise, you can check whether they are set up to the correct port in Backoffice Support Tools __________________________________________________________________________________________________ Upon login, once the user is logged in, the browser will ask for the installation of SaClient if the installed version is not the latest or it hasn't been previously installed. See more here.
description:
Log the customer out of the system all the way to the client login and make sure they are logged in on the right machine.  

Machine Login: 

  

If they open it from POS = DdDPOS 

If they open it on a BO machine = Backoffice 


   



  

Ask them to shut off printer, then restart POS (or PC), then turn printer on again. 


__________________________________________________________________________________________________


Otherwise, you can check whether they are set up to the correct port in Backoffice Support Tools


  
__________________________________________________________________________________________________



Upon login, once the user is logged in, the browser will ask for the installation of SaClient if the installed version is not the latest or it hasn't been previously installed. 

  

See more here.

title: Label printer - prints very slowly
text: Customer calls saying that it takes a long time to print labels. It does work, but takes around 1 minute of loading. To resolve this, open pathfinder in Windows and go to C:\SaClient\temp and find the file called Barcode.bat Rightclick on the file and select Edit The file should look like this when you open it: net use lpt3 \\%computername%\label /y copy c:\saclient\temp\barcode.dat %1 To resolve it you have to write "rem" in the start of the file, so it looks like below: rem net use lpt3 \\%computername%\label /y copy c:\saclient\temp\barcode.dat %1
description:
Customer calls saying that it takes a long time to print labels. 

It does work, but takes around 1 minute of loading. 

  

To resolve this, open pathfinder in Windows and go to C:\SaClient\temp and find the file called Barcode.bat 

  

Rightclick on the file and select Edit 

  

The file should look like this when you open it:  

  

net use lpt3 \\%computername%\label /y

copy c:\saclient\temp\barcode.dat %1 

  

To resolve it you have to write "rem" in the start of the file, so it looks like below: 

  

rem net use lpt3 \\%computername%\label /y

copy c:\saclient\temp\barcode.dat %1

title: Label printer prints last printed labels every time after login to back office
text: If a customer contacts that when they logged out of backoffice and logged in again,the label printer starts printing the last printed labels. This is furstrating for the customer and also misuse of their resources. The solution in such case to change the information in the initport.bat file. The initport.bat file can be accessed through the following path. Go to MyComputer->C: Drive->Saclient->initport.bat Right click on initport.bat file, Select edit, the file opens in Notepad and make sure the file include the following text mode %1: baud=9600 parity=n data=8 Save the file and asked the customer to log out and in again to backoffice to confirm that the labelprinter should not print the last printed labels this time.
description:
If a customer contacts that when they logged out of backoffice and logged in again,the label printer starts printing the last printed labels.

This is furstrating for the customer and also misuse of their resources.

The solution in such case to change the information in the initport.bat file.

The initport.bat file can be accessed through the following path.

Go to MyComputer->C: Drive->Saclient->initport.bat





Right click on initport.bat file, Select edit, the file opens in Notepad and make sure the file include the following text

mode %1: baud=9600 parity=n data=8

Save the file and asked the customer to log out and in again to backoffice to confirm that the labelprinter should not print the last printed labels this time.

title: Label printer prints extra white labels
text: Login to DdD backoffice Support Tools Open the menu "Edit / create system" Search for the customer: here i am using DdD køge Test Shop 1 Press "Edit selected client" on the right. In the next windows choose "client info" followed by "labels" Here you need to look for this line "no form feed" If there is no check mark then add it and press "update client" If it is already there then remove it and press "update client"and then add it again and press "update client" Afterwards turn off the label printer and have the customer open Backoffice again andthen turn on the label printer again.
description:
Login to DdD backoffice Support Tools


Open the menu "Edit / create system"


Search for the customer:  here i am using DdD køge Test Shop 1


Press "Edit selected client" on the right.

In the next windows choose "client info" followed by "labels"


Here you need to look for this line "no form feed"
If there is no check mark then add it and press "update client"
If it is already there then remove it and press "update client"and then add it again and press "update client"
Afterwards turn off the label printer and have the customer open Backoffice again andthen turn on the label printer again.
